{"title":"Urticaria y angioedema","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Dermatología/Urticaria y angioedema-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"- Urticaria y\\Nangioedema","guid":"BQZ1lVJrgnhIR3AVAVpN2Q","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Resumen","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"1. Definición","guid":"M11mzRIxcmgtGT6ILW1HSQ","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• Urticaria: Trastorno común (15–25% prevalencia) → habones pruriginosos con eritema epidérmico (1-48 h).","guid":"N0T_2D3hNjcWOh5kDIx5tA","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"• Angioedema: Edema subcutáneo, puede presentarse con o sin urticaria (40%).","guid":"GU5hPzeebQpV0kmeAhdLBg","children":[]}]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"2. Fisiopatología","guid":"CaA5GwVs_3dlR-IVetZViA","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"• Células Principales: Mastocitos.","guid":"QyqJdT4yunIU-J5VSDD_Cw","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"5","text":"• Mediadores: Histamina, leucotrienos, prostaglandinas → vasodilatación, extravasación plasmática.","guid":"EJ486l1ADmpJi0zkXp-GLA","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"5","text":"• Citoquinas: TNF, IL-4, IL-5 → respuestas inflamatorias tardías (4-8 h).","guid":"Psud3Aw1bct6-sbrMBuAow","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"3. Clasificación","guid":"NrwWlWgo0XANWtiEbgEWbQ","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"• Urticaria Aguda: <6 semanas, con/sin angioedema.","guid":"JgoHpyOU9ul6jZAiP1ho5w","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"9","text":"• Urticaria Crónica: ≥6 semanas, con/sin angioedema.","guid":"WzNj81Bf2cBBb7PtDpDKwA","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"• Crónica Espontánea: Sin estímulo identificable.","guid":"YpFMKG6I8nU7_hIJbDGFQw","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"11","text":"• Inducible: Estímulos físicos (dermatografismo, frío, calor, sol, presión).","guid":"c_Xx7CFF9B5nB9rMNyB7Yg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"14","parent":"1","text":"4. Angioedema","guid":"X3iukXwAeSF_UXptcBbrew","children":[{"id":"15","parent":"14","text":"• Mediado por Histamina: Alérgico, pseudoalérgico, idiopático.","guid":"WUCHi0jcx1FOtnGnGAwlZw","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"14","text":"• No Mediado por Histamina:","guid":"VRI1HEmxOJNIJ6YLC85Lsg","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"• Mediado por Bradicinina: Hereditario, adquirido, fármacos (IECA).","guid":"MdoKA1WCfo95z2IfV-QRqw","children":[]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"14","text":"• Complicación: Asfixia fatal por compromiso laríngeo.","guid":"eRd1eHRc8kEXPHqSVErZaw","children":[]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"1","text":"5. Tratamiento","guid":"RLzMAVisLn9i26QrJ04YKg","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"• Urticaria (Aguda/Crónica): Antihistamínicos H1 de 2ª generación (no sedantes, no incapacitantes).","guid":"RzUg9B7ZtjUTf51tOysS4A","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"• Angioedema:","guid":"QB-qU3qHeDlyS45CH5hY5A","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"• Evitar Desencadenantes.","guid":"dofxWnGdCK8Pr0RgT8h45Q","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"21","text":"• Angioedema Hereditario: Tratamientos específicos (ataques agudos, profilaxis).","guid":"OnnQAF5ltgdn1J5ND4wFHQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"1","text":"6. Diagnóstico\\Ny Manejo","guid":"KBbumi_8RFgbWlDPWfD4ng","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"• Urticaria: Evaluar duración, identificar estímulos, control con antihistamínicos.","guid":"BX7C5xUpsu4x1QpJfpY4YA","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"• Angioedema Sin Urticaria: Diferenciar mediado por histamina/no histamina → manejo específico según tipo.","guid":"CYalMEkRhNtS4RHLTkNxMQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"0","text":"Urticaria","guid":"STUdsjMBUBV5YPjWMkNSeg","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"1. Clasificación","guid":"VJZsLAkRJskkHecuFLYWfw","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"• Urticaria\\NCrónica (UC):","guid":"A5ifAhZpdXE0Tm9keiCQXQ","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• Prevalencia: 0.5–5%.","guid":"CAZ-IEP9s8RJ6QlCQoBOIQ","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"• Común en adultos (20-40 años), más en mujeres.","guid":"ImNpyzG9p49SDFM-SnpYZg","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"• UC Espontánea\\NCrónica (CSU):","guid":"Ybnr521mpA0ka1EEZziuzw","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"• Sin desencadenante externo.","guid":"ApBW-1ZAW01lzucvDBb8Kw","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"• ~45% con autoanticuerpos IgG contra IgE o receptor α-IgE en mastocitos y basófilos.","guid":"H1HgKDiv-PpaWm1dQQ-Tgg","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"• Asociación con anticuerpos antitiroideos (~27%) y otras enfermedades autoinmunes (AR, LES, etc.).","guid":"bmyu8U_r9rgqAmfQQwMbHQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"29","text":"• UC Inducible:","guid":"ZInEbwwHoQFWtkzhbJBCkA","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"• Estímulos físicos (dermatografismo, frío, calor, sol, presión, vibración).","guid":"WP0dgU4gTv5XuTGdXJW8hA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"28","text":"• Urticaria\\NAguda (UA):","guid":"UAVUxSCfViMvEJCxcmi-kA","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"• Duración <6 semanas.","guid":"Ulz9swEc4-884xb2NBbpmg","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"• Causas\\NComunes:","guid":"boOH_GFOZ_obT5hpcRPe9w","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"• Medicamentos (β-lactámicos, sulfonamidas, AINEs, opioides).","guid":"N47DRwEef5h9KtsjVuCjbw","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"40","text":"• Alimentos (leche, huevos, maní, mariscos).","guid":"Oc54k1eFSIAX8DbxKDsnhA","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"40","text":"• Infecciones virales, estrés, veneno de insectos.","guid":"J3E_OEHynsFrPkKiAG5cug","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"40","text":"• ~50% sin causa identificable (Urticaria Espontánea Aguda, ASU).","guid":"EBLtwEL3dD9dBBk-dJyyLw","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"• ~36% de ASU → CSU.","guid":"Tv8VQDO6Zh9hLPS_HwRqBQ","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"27","text":"2. Etiología","guid":"VFm8QhA9hXARbSiVJra59Q","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"• Urticaria\\NCrónica:","guid":"EVppX05QP4xazaOQf93xWw","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"• Autoinmune: IgG contra IgE o receptor α-IgE → liberación crónica de histamina.","guid":"L56nhnYdO_lw8dBTZy1qzg","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"47","text":"• Infecciosa: Hepatitis B/C, EBV, H. pylori, helmintos (papel limitado, excepto parasitosis).","guid":"dzu7km4cq3Y-Dg49MQo0JQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"50","parent":"46","text":"• Urticaria\\NInducible:","guid":"RaHz9lX-RS9ZRVupbRMzLg","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"• Estímulos físicos: dermatografismo, urticaria colinérgica, inducida por frío, solar, acuagénica, vibratoria, por ejercicio.","guid":"F_Dj8ESDnkttgY_oKAPRsA","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"50","text":"• Características de las Lesiones: Localizadas, resuelven en ~2 h (excepto urticaria por presión retardada).","guid":"B3sSikqFqSYcoIPgVnonyg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"53","parent":"27","text":"3. Diagnóstico","guid":"fkAPRX3NeJ91fpHPUpnLiA","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"• Historial Clínico y Examen Físico: Frecuencia, duración, patrón de lesiones, desencadenantes, respuesta a terapias, historia atópica.","guid":"Dgr-EAbrumV5UIV9H2Vnbw","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"53","text":"• Diagnóstico Diferencial: Urticaria vs. vasculitis urticarial, mastocitosis sistémica, otras enfermedades","guid":"VTv58VQeKQ0fQ1jLBNqhdw","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"53","text":"• Pruebas\\NDiagnósticas:","guid":"SjtlBxA1KR5sCAxFQXcgmQ","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"• Pruebas de Punción Cutánea (SPTs) e IgE específica: Confirmar urticaria aguda alérgica.","guid":"flHUlCoWGoNygVS-Q_PIig","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"• CSU: Hemograma, VSG/CRP, autoanticuerpos tiroideos, biopsia cutánea en casos atípicos.","guid":"ABRfskvGsGcxBvu4GAVDog","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"• Pruebas de Provocación: Confirman urticaria inducible (test de cubo de hielo, dermografómetro, etc.).","guid":"EEpOsx6Ii6FACRVTF8VhPQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"60","parent":"27","text":"4. Tratamiento","guid":"aQ40x1ypmTNuP4kIZ05EDQ","children":[{"id":"61","parent":"60","text":"• Primera Línea: Antihistamínicos H1 de 2ª generación.","guid":"WncR0mO-Gtc56A-VaIIP4g","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"60","text":"• Segunda Línea: Aumentar dosis de antihistamínicos (hasta 4x dosis estándar).","guid":"aqnVPDM4lRIH53dSP-XPLQ","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"60","text":"• Tercera Línea: Omalizumab (anti-IgE).","guid":"B1a-ICcq0B1EwHClUZIjJw","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"60","text":"• Cuarta Línea: Ciclosporina.","guid":"N1_5OzDIfOoTCUPANbHNzw","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"60","text":"• Otras Opciones: Corticoides orales (cursos cortos), antagonistas de receptores de leucotrienos\\N(montelukast), terapias inmunosupresoras/inmunomoduladoras para casos refractarios.","guid":"Wt6XbQWKmH55pZZZWvL3Hw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"66","parent":"0","text":"Angioedema","guid":"D6rpSGeggd4ZkZaHaiH7Gg","children":[{"id":"67","parent":"66","text":"1. Introducción","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"• Angioedema sin urticaria: Menos común, puede indicar condiciones graves (HAE, AAE, angioedema por IECA).","guid":"S16ctVN5phxSpAr9Nghx8g","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"• Fisiopatología: Liberación de mediadores vasoactivos (histamina, bradicinina) → ↑ permeabilidad vascular → edema.","guid":"BrI7LlqLgk917kEfDgj5Tg","children":[]}]},{"id":"70","parent":"66","text":"2. Clasificación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"• Mediado por\\NHistamina:","guid":"AbZSbDquscRfmxx1ORZLpw","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"• Alérgico, Pseudoalérgico, Idiopático.","guid":"a3cur3KkYDVuyBl2RlXGHA","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"71","text":"• Responde a antihistamínicos y corticosteroides.","guid":"eC74s2htr88hSL08SYBBmQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"74","parent":"70","text":"• Mediado por\\NBradicinina:","guid":"ExpB4BRA9_4rG9kxXE9fkw","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"• Hereditario (HAE): Autosómico dominante.\\NTipos:","guid":"R0JIEyR80gcOkrINVu0xWw","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"• HAE-1: ↓ C1-INH (85%).","guid":"DB1T5SgkSJRBDyx1V3vwmw","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"• HAE-2: C1-INH normal pero disfuncional (15%).","guid":"e53usBOzN3INhGKNAlAp3g","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"75","text":"• HAE-nC1-INH: C1-INH normal (mutación FXII).","guid":"bj65wQNyo6wQWSMtb_UMLQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"74","text":"• Adquirido (AAE): Asociado a enfermedades linfoproliferativas (tipo 1) o autoanticuerpos (tipo 2).","guid":"PiFVcW_0P6IpC1fUKZiEIA","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"74","text":"• Inducido por IECA: Frecuente, especialmente en mujeres, fumadores y afroamericanos. Ocurre por ↓ degradación de bradicinina.","guid":"Ypif2BfTcUpv7ko8WseYiw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"66","text":"3. Etiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"• HAE: Deficiencia o disfunción de C1-INH → exceso de bradicinina.","guid":"AEEhGRE3B3gkR9okE1ti-g","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"81","text":"• AAE: Deficiencia de C1-INH secundaria a linfoproliferación o autoanticuerpos.","guid":"JXf_dk9js1ZvqsKNbLpHiQ","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"81","text":"• Angioedema por IECA: Interferencia en la degradación de bradicinina.","guid":"c-CFXX49dJpDp3jkf_3ZQw","children":[]}]},{"id":"85","parent":"66","text":"4. Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"• Historia Clínica y Examen Físico: Localización del edema (cara, extremidades, abdomen), exclusión de urticaria, historia familiar.","guid":"JmG9LgS2pVpXecneIf-r3g","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"85","text":"• Pruebas de Laboratorio:","guid":"GGnczGT-LGskT9W8BqiWjg","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"• HAE/AAE: ↓ C4, ↓ función de C1-INH, ↓/Niveles normales de C1q.","guid":"aHDQFzSo-Ol2naK7JpIliA","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"87","text":"• Angioedema por IECA: C1-INH normal, evaluar para HAE/AAE si indicado.","guid":"JJ04jB-o-pBQKqmoBzXYZA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"90","parent":"66","text":"5. Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"91","parent":"90","text":"• Ataques Agudos:","guid":"N3xr2kAY8-Vh_XDvN72M9A","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"• Reemplazo de C1-INH, Icatibant (bloqueador del receptor de bradicinina), Ecallantide (inhibidor de calicreína plasmática).","guid":"UU_7XQZFSxRLGO_udsf61A","children":[]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"90","text":"• Profilaxis a Corto Plazo (STP):","guid":"Vaj-ajrDsntjgkJdSYmDxw","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"• C1-INH (Cinryze, Berinert), andrógenos atenuados (Danazol).","guid":"OQEnFScpu0JJh10KX2LkQw","children":[]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"90","text":"• Profilaxis a Largo Plazo (LTP):","guid":"K-BgnCEBJugBYpAhREo9aA","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"• C1-INH, andrógenos atenuados (Danazol), ácido tranexámico (embarazo, intolerancia a andrógenos).","guid":"Bf9TUyWyZd1K8tP2bnAjaw","children":[]}]}]}]}]},"node_count":96,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Dermatología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Dermatología","filename":"Urticaria y angioedema-2024","id":"map_471","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Urticaria y angioedema-2024"}